===
How to install the s-net(r) tools for the HDLC Daemon
===

For GNU/Linux:
---
Preparations:
- First install the HDLC Daemon from https://github.com/Strunzdesign/hdlcd.
- Follow the HDLCd installation guide from file INSTALL.
- Following that guide assures that your toolchain is complete.

To compile the s-net(r) tools, just follow these steps:
1.) git clone https://github.com/Strunzdesign/snet-tools.git
2.) cd snet-tools
3.) mkdir build
4.) cd build
5.) cmake ..
6.) make
7.) make install (as root)

All binaries will be installed to "/usr/local/bin/".



For Microsoft Windows 7:
---
Preparations:
- First install the HDLC Daemon from https://github.com/Strunzdesign/hdlcd.
- Follow the HDLCd installation guide from file INSTALL.
- Following that guide assures that your toolchain is complete.

To compile the s-net(r) tools and to install them along with the header files, just follow these steps:
1.) Go to your projects' folder and open a shell there
2.) git clone https://github.com/Strunzdesign/snet-tools.git
3.) cd snet-tools
4.) mkdir build
5.) cd build
6.) Pick yourself a directory to install the compiled files, e.g., consider C:\snet-tools
7.) Remember the directory where you installed the HDLC Daemon, e.g., C:\hdlcd
8.) cmake -G "MinGW Makefiles" -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/c/snet-tools -DHDLCD_INCLUDE_DIR=/c/hdlcd/include ..
9.) If you get an error message on step 8, repeat step 9 once
10.) make
11.) make install

The "snet-tools" binaries will be installed to "C:\snet-tools\bin\".

Have fun :-)
